I am a new user for Cantera.. I was checking equilibrium conditions 
for certain reactions. I have a problem. I carried out a reaction by 
specifying a temperature and pressure. I used equilibrate function 
at constant temperature and volume. After this I checked the 
pressure again. It was equal to the initial pressure specified. The 
total number of moles are changing in the reaction, and I had 
carried out the equilibrium at constant temperature and volume. Then 
why is the pressure same as initially specified? 
Ajay
